---
export const prerender = true;
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Pillar 3 Disclosure" description="Pillar 3 capital adequacy and risk management disclosure — Hengistbury Investment Partners LLP.">

  <div class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <a href="/disclosures" class="back-link">← Disclosures</a>
      <p class="eyebrow">Regulatory Disclosure</p>
      <h1>Pillar 3 Disclosure</h1>
      <p class="meta">Hengistbury Investment Partners LLP &mdash; Year ended 31 December 2023</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <article class="disclosure-body">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="doc-grid">
        <nav class="doc-toc">
          <p class="toc-label">Contents</p>
          <ol>
            <li><a href="#background">Background and Basis of Disclosure</a></li>
            <li><a href="#risk-management">Risk Management Objectives and Policies</a></li>
            <li><a href="#capital-resources">Capital Resources</a></li>
            <li><a href="#capital-requirements">Capital Requirements</a></li>
            <li><a href="#remuneration">Remuneration</a></li>
          </ol>
          <div class="toc-footer">
            <a href="/disclosures" class="back-link-sm">All disclosures</a>
          </div>
        </nav>

        <div class="doc-content">
          <section id="background">
            <h2>1. Background and Basis of Disclosure</h2>
            <p>
              This document sets out the Pillar 3 disclosures of Hengistbury Investment Partners LLP
              (&ldquo;the Firm&rdquo;) for the year ended 31 December 2023. The disclosures have been prepared
              in accordance with the requirements of the UK Capital Requirements Regulation
              (&ldquo;UK CRR&rdquo;) and related provisions of the Prudential Sourcebook for Banks, Building
              Societies and Investment Firms (&ldquo;BIPRU&rdquo;) as they apply to the Firm.
            </p>
            <p>
              The Firm is authorised and regulated by the Financial Conduct Authority (&ldquo;FCA&rdquo;) and
              is classified as a BIPRU limited licence firm for regulatory capital purposes. The
              Firm&rsquo;s principal activities comprise alternative investment fund management.
            </p>
            <p>
              Pillar 3 disclosures are intended to complement the minimum capital requirements
              established under Pillar 1 and the supervisory review process under Pillar 2. They
              are designed to promote market discipline by providing market participants with key
              information on a firm&rsquo;s risk exposures and risk management processes.
            </p>
            <p>
              These disclosures are made on an annual basis and are reviewed and approved by the
              Firm&rsquo;s management. The Firm is not part of a group for regulatory purposes.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section id="risk-management">
            <h2>2. Risk Management Objectives and Policies</h2>
            <h3>2.1 Overview</h3>
            <p>
              The Firm&rsquo;s approach to risk management is designed to identify, assess, monitor and
              control risks to which the Firm is, or may be, exposed. The Firm&rsquo;s management is
              responsible for implementing and maintaining an appropriate risk management framework.
            </p>

            <h3>2.2 Credit Risk</h3>
            <p>
              Credit risk arises from the possibility that a counterparty will fail to meet its
              obligations in accordance with agreed terms. The Firm&rsquo;s credit risk exposure is
              limited principally to cash and cash equivalents held at regulated financial
              institutions and receivables from managed accounts. The Firm monitors counterparty
              exposures on an ongoing basis.
            </p>

            <h3>2.3 Market Risk</h3>
            <p>
              The Firm does not take proprietary positions in securities or other financial
              instruments in the course of its regulated activities. Market risk at the entity
              level is accordingly limited. The Firm&rsquo;s revenue is linked to assets under
              management, which may vary with market conditions.
            </p>

            <h3>2.4 Operational Risk</h3>
            <p>
              Operational risk is the risk of loss arising from inadequate or failed internal
              processes, people and systems or from external events. The Firm maintains documented
              operational procedures, segregation of duties, and appropriate controls to mitigate
              operational risk. Business continuity and disaster recovery arrangements are in place.
            </p>

            <h3>2.5 Liquidity Risk</h3>
            <p>
              The Firm maintains liquid capital resources in excess of its regulatory capital
              requirement. Liquidity is monitored on a regular basis and the Firm is satisfied
              that it maintains sufficient liquidity to meet its obligations as they fall due.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section id="capital-resources">
            <h2>3. Capital Resources</h2>
            <p>
              The Firm&rsquo;s capital resources consist entirely of Tier 1 capital. As at 31 December
              2023, the Firm held capital resources in excess of its regulatory capital requirement.
              The Firm&rsquo;s Tier 1 capital comprises members&rsquo; capital, retained earnings and other
              reserves.
            </p>
            <p>
              Detailed financial information is set out in the Firm&rsquo;s annual accounts filed at
              Companies House. The Firm confirms that its capital resources were sufficient at all
              times during the reporting period to meet the applicable regulatory minimum.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section id="capital-requirements">
            <h2>4. Capital Requirements</h2>
            <p>
              The Firm is classified as a BIPRU limited licence firm. Accordingly, its Pillar 1
              capital requirement is calculated as the higher of:
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li>the Base Capital Requirement (&pound;50,000);</li>
              <li>the sum of the Firm&rsquo;s Credit Risk Capital Requirement and its Fixed Overheads Requirement; and</li>
              <li>the Firm&rsquo;s Fixed Overheads Requirement.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              The Firm conducts an Internal Capital Adequacy Assessment Process (&ldquo;ICAAP&rdquo;) on an
              annual basis, or more frequently where circumstances require. The ICAAP identifies
              and assesses all material risks to the Firm and determines the appropriate level of
              capital to be held.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section id="remuneration">
            <h2>5. Remuneration</h2>
            <p>
              Detailed information regarding the Firm&rsquo;s remuneration policies and practices is
              set out in our separate <a href="/disclosures/remuneration">Remuneration Policy Disclosure</a>.
              As a limited licence BIPRU firm, the Firm is subject to proportionate application
              of the remuneration requirements under MIFIDPRU.
            </p>
          </section>

          <div class="doc-footer">
            <p>Published: January 2024 &bull; Covers year ended 31 December 2023</p>
            <p>
              Hengistbury Investment Partners LLP &bull; Partnership No: OC365747 &bull;
              Authorised and regulated by the Financial Conduct Authority
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    background: var(--navy);
    padding: 3rem 0 4rem;
  }

  .back-link {
    display: inline-block;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .back-link:hover { color: var(--gold); }

  .eyebrow {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--gold);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .page-hero h1 { color: var(--white); margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }

  .meta {
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }

  .disclosure-body { padding: 4rem 0; background: var(--white); }

  .doc-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 220px 1fr;
    gap: 4rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .doc-toc {
    position: sticky;
    top: 90px;
  }

  .toc-label {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--mid-gray);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .doc-toc ol {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
    border-left: 2px solid var(--border);
    padding-left: 0;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .doc-toc a {
    display: block;
    padding: 0.45rem 0.75rem;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: var(--mid-gray);
    border-left: 2px solid transparent;
    margin-left: -2px;
    line-height: 1.4;
    transition: color 0.15s, border-color 0.15s;
  }

  .doc-toc a:hover { color: var(--navy); border-left-color: var(--gold); }

  .toc-footer { border-top: 1px solid var(--border); padding-top: 1rem; }

  .back-link-sm {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--mid-gray);
  }

  .back-link-sm:hover { color: var(--gold); }

  /* Document content */
  .doc-content section { margin-bottom: 3rem; }

  .doc-content h2 {
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    color: var(--navy);
  }

  .doc-content h3 {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--navy);
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .doc-content p {
    color: #444;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .doc-content ul {
    color: #444;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .doc-content li { margin-bottom: 0.35rem; }

  .doc-content a { color: var(--gold); }
  .doc-content a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

  .doc-footer {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding-top: 2rem;
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }

  .doc-footer p {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--mid-gray);
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .doc-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .doc-toc { position: static; }
  }
</style>
